      <abstract>
        <p>Marius Fernandez, Marseille artist, makes ceramic vases; photos (S) (Currents)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The architect Peter Merino is one New Yorker snapping up vases by Marius Fernandez, a Marseilles artist. A 20-inch one is about $2,200; yard-high vases, above, are about $4,800, at Galerie Aittouares, 2 rue des Beaux-Arts; 011-33-1-40-51-87-46.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The architect Peter Merino is one New Yorker snapping up vases by Marius Fernandez, a Marseilles artist. A 20-inch one is about $2,200; yard-high vases, above, are about $4,800, at Galerie Aittouares, 2 rue des Beaux-Arts; 011-33-1-40-51-87-46.</p>
        <p>CURRENTS: PARIS -- CERAMICS  Correction:  June 15, 2000, Thursday  A report in the Currents column last Thursday about a New York architect who buys vases by a Marseilles artist, Marius Fernandez, misspelled the buyer's surname. He is Peter Marino, not Merino.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="correction_text">
        <p>Correction: June 15, 2000, Thursday</p>
        <p>A report in the Currents column last Thursday about a New York architect who buys vases by a Marseilles artist, Marius Fernandez, misspelled the buyer's surname. He is Peter Marino, not Merino.</p>
        <p>&lt;br&gt;</p>
      </block>
